A vintage 1960s-style illustration showing two massive ocean waves—one deep indigo blue, one burnished gold—crashing together in the center of the composition, their collision creating not chaos but a perfectly calm, crystalline sphere of water suspended at the meeting point. The sphere reflects a serene landscape within it. The sky transitions from stormy clouds on both outer edges to a clear, warm sunset glow behind the central sphere. The waves are rendered with bold, sweeping brushstrokes reminiscent of Japanese woodblock prints merged with mid-century American commercial art. Rich, saturated colors with subtle paper texture throughout.
